The species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gutirrez, 1999" authorityName="Gutirrez" authorityYear="1999" box="[670,988,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Ectobiidae" genus="Leuropeltis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hebardi">
<emphasis box="[670,797,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">L. hebardi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gutirrez" box="[811,988,189,215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" refString="Gutirrez, E. (1999) The cockroach genus Leuropeltis Hebard (Dictyoptera: Blattellidae: Pseudophyllodromiinae) with a new species from South America. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 149, 71 - 75." type="journal article" year="1999">
Gutirrez, 
<number box="[929,988,189,215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the configuration of the median projection on the apex of the subgenital plate, but differs in the configuration of the median sclerite.
</paragraph>
